":"Prestbury, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bradshaw","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the three places called Bradshaw in Lancashire, Yorkshire, and Derbyshire, from Old English <i>brād</i> ‘broad’ + <i>sceaga</i> ‘thicket’."],"variants":[{"name":"Brayshaw","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): variant of   Bradshaw  , reflecting the local Yorkshire pronunciation."]}]},{"name":"Rondle","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>roundel</i> (Old French <i>rondel</i>), a diminutive of <i>round(e)</i> ‘rotund, plump’. Compare   Round  .","English: perhaps from the personal name <i>Rondulf</i>, a West Midlands variant of <i>Randulf</i>. See   Randolph   and   Randall  .","English: habitational name from Randall Wood in Shorne (Kent), from Old French <i>rondel</i> ‘circle, something circular’."],"variants":[{"name":"Rundel","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hermann.","German: from <i>Ru(o)nelin</i>, a pet form of an ancient Germanic personal name based on <i>rūn</i> ‘secret, rune, cryptogram’.","English: nickname from Old French <i>rondel</i>, a diminutive of <i>round(e)</i> ‘rotund, plump’. Compare   Rundle  ."]},{"name":"Round","meanings":["English (Worcestershire and Staffordshire): nickname for a plump person, from Middle English <i>round(e)</i> (Old French <i>rond</i>) ‘rotund, plump’ (from Latin <i>rotundus</i>)."]},{"name":"Rundall","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: medieval vernacular form of   Randolf .  This was in common use as a given name into the 17th century and gave rise to a surname. In modern use the given name is often a transferred use of this surname."]},{"name":"Runnells","meanings":["English (Cornwall): variant of   Rundle  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i> and loss of medial <i>-d-</i>. This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Rundell","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Rundle  .","Swedish: ornamental name composed of the element <i>rund</i> ‘round’ + the suffix <i>-ell</i>, a derivative of the Latin adjectival ending <i>-elius</i>.","Americanized form of German   Rundel  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Rondle Bradshaw was born in 1563, in Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert Blackshaw, was 37 and his mother, Ellen Waynewrighte, was 29. He married Lady Blackshaw in 1585, in Prestbury, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1592, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 29."},"et":{"1563–1592":"1563–1592","1556–1615":"1556–1615","1565–1619":"1565–1619","1565–Female":"1565–Surnud","1589–1661":"1589–1661","1526–1590":"1526–1590","1535–Female":"1535–Surnud","1592":"1592","1 June 1590":"1. juuni 1590","1590":"1590","1535":"1535","1589":"1589","1556":"1556","1565":"1565","1563":"1563","1585":"1585","1661":"1661","1619":"1619","1615":"1615","1526":"1526","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mobberley, Cheshire, England":"Mobberley, Cheshire, England","Prestbury, Cheshire, England":"Prestbury, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Prestbury, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Prestbury, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1563–1592":"1563–1592","1556–1615":"1556–1615","1565–1619":"1565–1619","1565–Female":"1565–Kuollut","1589–1661":"1589–1661","1526–1590":"1526–1590","1535–Female":"1535–Kuollut","1592":"1592","1 June 1590":"1. kesäkuuta 1590","1590":"1590","1535":"1535","1589":"1589","1556":"1556","1565":"1565","1563":"1563","1585":"1585","1661":"1661","1619":"1619","1615":"1615","1526":"1526","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England,